news.title: Ludhiana: Audit & accounts department orders illegal buildings' checking
news.para: Around five years ago, the local bodies department additional chief secretary had ordered action against illegal buildings, but the directions were hardly implemented, causing loss of Rs 100 crore to the MC and the Punjab government.

news.title: Green buildings in Nashik to get 1% property tax concession
news.para: Municipal commissioner Kailas Jadhav told TOI that housing societies treating waste through compost or biogas plants will get the rebate.

news.title: Nagpur: Standing committee to decide on property tax revision on Feb 8
news.para: Citing provision 99 of Maharashtra Municipal Corporation (MMC) Act, the department said that the tax structure for the next financial year should be tabled before the general body meeting before February 20.

news.title: Delhi: Last chance to go for 18,335 flats on offer under special DDA scheme
news.para: The authority had launched the scheme on December 24, 2021, with 18,335 flats on offer. Of these, 11,452 were one-bedroom flats in the lower income group (LIG) category, with cost ranging between Rs 14.1 lakh and Rs 41.1 lakh.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body order asking owners to surrender properties is arbitrary: HC
news.para: Justice Hemant Chandanagoudar said the Supreme Court has already held that the owner of immovable property cannot be deprived of h/her property by a mere executive order, sans any specific legal authority or support by competent legislation.

news.title: Institutional investors pumping more capital into residential realty
news.para: The combination of key factors, such as record-low interest rates, pandemic-driven realisation of the need for home ownership, developer incentives, and increased buyer confidence, bodes well for the residential sector.

news.title: Land reserved for green belt can't be allowed for raising any construction: NGT
news.para: The observations came while hearing a plea complaining inaction of statutory authorities in the protection of Laxmi Tal and the nearby area declared as 'green belt/green park' in Master Plan 2021 of Jhansi in Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Mysuru civic body wants to provide B Khata to the 50,000 revenue houses
news.para: Mysuru City Corporation wants to add properties without any Khatas to the B register to acquire income from taxes. Will government approve?

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body extends property tax amnesty scheme till February-end
news.para: The NMMC had rolled out the scheme for two months with effect from October 1, 2021. Later, the scheme was extended to January 31, 2022.

news.title: Geotagging of properties Ahmedabad civic body's priority
news.para: Also being put in place are emergency call boxes which is being put in place for citizen’s security for timely information and emergency response, claims the AMC official.

news.title: CHB sends reminder to state govts, PGI & Chandigarh admin on money for high-end flats
news.para: The participants have been asked to pay the 25% amount in advance, a request made numerous times but not heeded over the last one-and-a-half years.

news.title: DTCP team visits NBCC Green View, ask buyers to vacate as cracks appear in buildings
news.para: Officials said the residents and the NBCC representatives had been asked to give in writing the issues and solutions before a meeting with deputy commissioner Yash Garg on Tuesday to decide on the future course of action.

news.title: Rajasthan: Cancelled applications for lease deeds to be reviewed
news.para: An official said, “The move will not only give a fresh lease to the plot owners, but also help local bodies to achieve its target. There are several cases, which are rejected due to small technical issues. After resolving those problems, lease deeds will be issued.”

news.title: Promises, but no roadmap for homebuyers in Noida
news.para: Wide roads, metro access, educational institutions and an abundance of housing — as Noida developed over the years, lakhs of homebuyers invested here. More than a decade later, many buyers have been handed flats and they have settled in the city with their families.

news.title: Mumbai: Construction boom is on despite unsold inventory piling up
news.para: Last year, the BMC approved new real estate projects with a built-up area totalling about 15 crore sq ft. This area, according to a ballpark estimate, is roughly the size of 15 Nariman Points.
